[2;36m│[0m **XSS Vulnerability Analysis:**                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m The `/page` endpoint accepts a `name` parameter and renders it directly into [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m an `<img src="{name}">` tag without proper sanitization. This is a           [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **DOM-based XSS vulnerability in an img src attribute**.                     [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **Input Validation Results:**                                                [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - `<` character is blocked                                                   [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - `(` character is blocked                                                   [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - `)` character is blocked                                                   [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - Single quotes (`'`) are NOT blocked                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - Double quotes (`"`) are NOT blocked                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - URL encoding/decoding is applied                                           [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m - `X-XSS-Protection: 0` header is set (browser XSS filter disabled)          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **Key Observation - Error Message:**                                         [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m When submitting a simple payload like `name=test`, the application responded [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m with:                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m ```                                                                          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m "Oops! You did an alert with TypeError: Attempting to change the setter of   [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m an unconfigurable property. instead of "XSS""                                [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m ```                                                                          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m This indicates:                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. The application expects an alert with the exact string "XSS"              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. There's JavaScript executing to validate the payload                      [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 3. Some destination URLs (even simple strings) trigger JavaScript execution  [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **The Vulnerability:**                                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m The name parameter is reflected inside `<img src="{name}">`. A payload can:  [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. Use `onerror` event handler to execute JavaScript when the image fails to [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m load                                                                         [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. The src will be invalid causing the error handler to fire                 [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 3. Need to bypass `(` and `)` filters to execute `alert("XSS")`              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **Response Headers:**                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m ```                                                                          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m x-xss-protection: 0  ← Browser XSS filter disabled                           [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m server: Werkzeug/1.0.1 Python/2.7.18                                         [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m content-type: text/html; charset=utf-8                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m ```                                                                          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **Next Steps for Exploitation:**                                             [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. Bypass the `(` and `)` filter using alternative JavaScript syntax:        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m    - `alert`60`` - template literal as argument                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m    - `alert\`XSS\`` - backtick template literal                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m    - `throw~alert~1` - expression-based execution                            [2;36m│[0m
